					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: The Failure Fetish</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-03-25T16:10:18+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">March 25, 2014 12:10 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">March 25, 2014 12:10 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/03/25/today-in-small-business-the-failure-fetish/" data-title="Today in Small Business: The Failure Fetish" data-description="How to start a delivery business. How to find happiness after selling a business. Is a third of all Internet traffic bogus?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ SurePayroll is <a href="//www.accountingtoday.com/news/surepayroll-sees-steady-optimism-at-small-businesses-70082-1.html">seeing optimism</a> among its small-business clients.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The consensus of 48 economists surveyed by the National Association for Business Economics is that bad weather cut first-quarter growth &#8212; but that <a href="//www.azcentral.com/story/money/business/2014/03/24/economists-see-good-growth-year/6820579/">growth could exceed</a> 3 percent by year&#8217;s end.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Opportunities</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Yoga classes for owners and their pets are a sign that <a href="//www.csmonitor.com/Business/2014/0324/Six-signs-pets-are-the-economy-s-new-big-spenders/Pet-insurance">pets are</a> the economy&#8217;s new big spenders.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Kobe Bryant has <a href="//espn.go.com/los-angeles/nba/story/_/id/10663439/kobe-bryant-announces-new-company-kobe-inc">formed his own company</a>, Kobe Inc., and is building a team to start new businesses and invest in others.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Some car companies are looking at using <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/03/25/business/car-companies-take-expertise-in-battery-power-beyond-the-garage.html?">energy from car </a><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/03/25/business/car-companies-take-expertise-in-battery-power-beyond-the-garage.html?">batteries</a> to power houses.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Social Media<br />
</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A third <a href="//online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304026304579453253860786362?">of all Internet traffic</a> is bogus, according to a trade group.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The average sponsored post on Tumblr <a href="//contently.com/strategist/2014/03/19/the-average-sponsored-post-on-tumblr-gets-reblogged-10000-times-heres-why/?">gets reblogged</a> 10,000 times.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A clothing designer explains how it <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/wren-first-kiss-viral-success-2014-3">made that viral video</a> of strangers kissing and increased sales by nearly 14,000 percent. <span id="more-83839"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Finance</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ One in three Americans hasn&#8217;t <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/economics/2014/03/24/one-in-three-of-americans-hasnt-been-to-the-bank-in-at-least-6-months/?">been to a bank</a> in six months.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ GrubHub, an online food delivery service, says its public offering <a href="//www.nbcnews.com/business/consumer/grubhub-says-ipo-could-value-food-deliverer-1-7-billion-n60586">could value</a> the company at $1.7 billion, and Box, an online storage start-up, <a href="//www.firmology.com/2014/03/24/online-storage-startup-box-files-for-250-million-ipo/">files for</a> a $250 million offering.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ An entrepreneur with a âfishyâ idea for making beef more healthful is <a href="//denver.cbslocal.com/2014/03/24/colorado-scientists-entrepreneur-seek-crowd-funds/">turning to crowdfunding</a> to pay for research.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A Federal Reserve governor <a href="//www.thestreet.com/story/12540546/1/crowdfunding-gets-feds-attention.html">cites examples</a> of crowdfunding helping communities.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Start Up</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here is Inc.âs bracket of the <a href="//www.inc.com/diana-ransom/coolest-college-startups-Inc-announces-elite-eight-.html">coolest college start-ups</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Entrepreneurship</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Kevin Roose writes that failure is increasingly becoming <a href="//nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2014/03/silicon-valley-failure-fetish.html">a badge of honor</a>, especially in Silicon Valley, which has a &#8220;failure fetish.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A girl scout sets a record by <a href="//www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2014/03/24/oklahoma-girl-scout-record-cookie-sales/6847913/">selling 18,107 boxes</a> of cookies.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Management</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Mark Cuban claims that the &#8220;greedy&#8221; National Football League <a href="//mavsblog.dallasnews.com/2014/03/mark-cuban-even-the-nfl-can-have-too-much-of-a-good-thing.html/">is 10 years</a> from implosion.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Baseball card stores have <a href="//www.northjersey.com/news/business/as-baseball-card-sales-drop-sellers-look-to-the-stars-1.750153">been in a decade-long slide</a>, forcing some owners to scramble and learn valuable business lessons.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here are a few tips for setting <a href="//www.business-opportunities.biz/2014/03/24/setting-up-your-own-delivery-driver-business/">up your own</a> delivery business.</p>
